		{
			"id": 1,
			"parent": 5,
			"text": "Word-sense recognition and disambiguation ( WERD ) is the task ",
			"relation": "bg-goal"
		},
		{
			"id": 2,
			"parent": 1,
			"text": "of identifying word phrases and their senses in natural language text . <S>",
			"relation": "elab-addition"
		},
		{
			"id": 3,
			"parent": 4,
			"text": "Though it is well understood how to disambiguate noun phrases , ",
			"relation": "contrast"
		},
		{
			"id": 4,
			"parent": 5,
			"text": "this task is much less studied for verbs and verbal phrases . <S>",
			"relation": "bg-goal"
		},
		{
			"id": 5,
			"parent": 0,
			"text": "We present Werdy , a framework for WERD with particular focus on verbs and verbal phrases . <S>",
			"relation": "ROOT"
		},
		{
			"id": 6,
			"parent": 5,
			"text": "Our framework first identifies multi-word expressions ",
			"relation": "elab-addition"
		},
		{
			"id": 7,
			"parent": 6,
			"text": "based on the syntactic structure of the sentence ; ",
			"relation": "bg-general"
		},
		{
			"id": 8,
			"parent": 6,
			"text": "this allows us to recognize both contiguous and non-contiguous phrases . <S>",
			"relation": "elab-addition"
		},
		{
			"id": 9,
			"parent": 6,
			"text": "We then generate a list of candidate senses for each word or phrase , ",
			"relation": "joint"
		},
		{
			"id": 10,
			"parent": 9,
			"text": "using novel syntactic and semantic pruning techniques . <S>",
			"relation": "elab-addition"
		},
		{
			"id": 11,
			"parent": 6,
			"text": "We also construct and leverage a new resource of pairs of senses for verbs and their object arguments . <S>",
			"relation": "joint"
		},
		{
			"id": 12,
			"parent": 15,
			"text": "Finally , we feed the so-obtained candidate senses into standard word-sense disambiguation ( WSD ) methods , ",
			"relation": "manner-means"
		},
		{
			"id": 13,
			"parent": 12,
			"text": "and boost their precision and recall . <S>",
			"relation": "joint"
		},
		{
			"id": 14,
			"parent": 15,
			"text": "Our experiments indicate ",
			"relation": "attribution"
		},
		{
			"id": 15,
			"parent": 5,
			"text": "that Werdy significantly increases the performance of existing WSD methods . <S>",
			"relation": "evaluation"
		}
	]
